Then open http://localhost:5065. Port is configurable via `PORT` (defaults to 5065). Full instructions and a quick walkthrough are in `README.md`.

## Two things worth flagging
- **One native dependency by design.** I dropped `connect-sqlite3` (which pulls in a second native module whose prebuilt binaries lag on Node 24/Windows and is the most likely cause of an `npm install` failure) and instead back sessions with a small SQLite store (`session-store.js`) on the same connection. So only `better-sqlite3` compiles.
- **Unverified at runtime.** I could not execute `npm install` or start the server here. If `better-sqlite3`'s prebuilt binary isn't available for your exact Node 24.16 build, `npm install` will try to compile it (needs Windows build tools). If that happens, tell me and I can switch the data layer to Node 24's built-in `node:sqlite` to eliminate the native build entirely.

