## What I built

A complete, secure Q&A site under `qa-site/`. All source files are written and the structure is ready to run.

**Stack:** Express + EJS + SQLite (`better-sqlite3`), sessions in SQLite, bcrypt, helmet, express-validator.

**Core features**
- Register / login / logout
- Ask questions, post answers
- One up/down vote per user per item (UNIQUE constraint; re-voting toggles or flips)
- Question owner accepts exactly one answer (transactional)
- Answers sorted: accepted → score → oldest

**Security (mapped to your requirements)**
- **SQL injection** — every query is a prepared statement with bound params (`src/models.js`)
- **Passwords** — bcrypt cost 12 with per-password salt
- **XSS** — EJS auto-escaping (`<%= %>`) + strict CSP with no inline scripts
- **CSRF** — synchronizer token verified on all non-safe requests, constant-time compare (`src/middleware/csrf.js`)
- **Access control / IDOR** — owner checks + integer id validation on accept/vote routes
- **Session cookies** — `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` (configurable for HTTPS), session regenerated on login to stop fixation
- **Headers** — helmet
- **Error handling** — real errors logged server-side, only generic message to client
- **Secrets** — read from env (`SESSION_SECRET` required; app refuses to start without it); `.env.example` provided
- Bonus: rate-limiting on auth, generic login errors to prevent user enumeration

## To run it

```powershell
cd qa-site
npm install          # ← this is what needs your approval (compiles better-sqlite3 + bcrypt)
Copy-Item .env.example .env
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(48).toString('hex'))"   # paste into SESSION_SECRET in .env
npm start
```

Then open http://localhost:5065.

